# -- MIRROMIROUS: Mirromirous Headband
planarartifice.research.mirromirous_headband.title=Mirromirous Headband
planarartifice.research.mirromirous_headband.stage.1=The original headband of curiosity has about run its course. As my knowledge continues to expand, the hunger for it grows as well.
planarartifice.research.mirromirous_headband.stage.2=Using some of my new materials, I have managed to build an upgraded version of the headband. It is twice as effective, and is able to draw in even more experience.

# -- MIRROMIROUS: Mirrored Amulet
planarartifice.research.mirrored_amulet.title=Mirrored Amulet
planarartifice.research.mirrored_amulet.stage.1=Death, in this world, is an inconvenience. The further I travel, the more likely I am to have uncommon or difficult to find items, and the more likely I am to die. The further away I die, the harder it becomes to recover my items. A way to keep all of my items intact after death would be incredibly useful in essentially every situation.
planarartifice.research.mirrored_amulet.stage.2=[WIP]

# -- MIRROMIROUS: Planar Infusion Enchantment
planarartifice.research.planar_infusion_enchantment.title=Planar Infusion Enchantment
planarartifice.research.planar_infusion_enchantment.stage.1=My thaumaturgy has come a long way since I originally invented infusion enchantments, and I now have access to a wider variety of materials and expertise. Many interesting ideas and concepts have come to my mind, which should hopefully be useful to me.
planarartifice.research.planar_infusion_enchantment.stage.2=I have created a few new infusion enchantments. Much like the original ones, some enchantments can be applied multiple times to the same item, but each rank has an increased essentia cost when crafted.<BR>Each different infusion enchantment on the item also increases the cost by 33% and has an increased chance of giving it the Warping property.<PAGE>§oMetaphize§r<DIV>Experience dropped from slain creatures will instead be converted into aura vis.<BR>The amount converted is 30% of experience per level (90% at max level).<DIV>§oRanks§r: 1-3<BR>§oTarget§r: weapon<PAGE>§oMirrored§r<DIV>The tool can be linked to a magic mirror when I sneak and right-click it. All drops obtained with that tool (from breaking blocks or slaying creatures) are transported directly to the linked mirror.<BR>I can unlink the tool from the mirror if I sneak and right-click on it again.<DIV>§oRanks§r: none<BR>§oTarget§r: axe, hoe, shovel, pickaxe, weapon
